00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:16,940
And this is the SSL connection could not be establishment.

44
00:03:16,940 --> 00:03:20,090
That means we don't have the remote certification.

45
00:03:20,090 --> 00:03:23,000
And this is the invalid according to the validation procedure.

46
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:30,500
This error happens due to ASP.Net core Https development certificate not being trusted by the client.

47
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,720
In our case, client is basket API.

48
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:40,760
When making call to the gRPC server discount gRPC, the asp.net https development certificate is required.

49
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,340
So how we can solve this problem?

50
00:03:43,340 --> 00:03:51,110
We can solve this problem to configure gRPC client in basket API to bypassing SSL certificate validations.

51
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:56,780
And this is done by modifying the configure primary Http message handler method.

52
00:03:56,780 --> 00:04:02,900
For that purpose, I'm going to open Visual Studio and go to the basket API programs case.

53
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:09,440
If you open the Program.cs and go to the configuration of the gRPC services here, you can see that

54
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:14,750
we would like to bypass the SSL certificate validation for that purpose.

55
00:04:14,750 --> 00:04:18,589
There is very good method extension for the configuration.

56
00:04:18,589 --> 00:04:23,690
I'm going to edit this configuration after these builder services at gRPC client.

57
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:31,160
In here I'm going to add this line of code which is the configure primary Http message handler method,

58
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:38,090
and specifying the Http client handler, and say that you can bypass the server certificate, custom

59
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:44,780
validation callback and accept any server certificate validators in our gRPC settings.

60
00:04:44,780 --> 00:04:51,380
But this setup is typically used for the development purpose and you should not be used in production

61
00:04:51,380 --> 00:04:53,540
environment due to security risks.

62
00:04:54,350 --> 00:05:00,380
So with this configuration we have fixed the SSL certification exception and we will continue our test.

